The union says criminals are aware of internal challenges faced by many police stations which include understaffing. JOHANNESBURG - Two police officers are among 11 people arrested after a foiled diamond heist. The suspects were taken in after a gun battle in Bryanston, Johannesburg on Saturday. The task force, including SAPS units, was acting on a tip-off. READ: CIT Heists: Crime Intelligence Unit activated The suspects arrived in three vehicles, including a police bakkie. Police confronted the perpetrators and a gunfight ensued. Two suspects were injured in the shootout. READ: Police reservist arrested for Boksburg cash heist The suspects are expected to appear in the Randburg Magistrate's Court on Tuesday. They face a range of charges including conspiracy to commit robbery and attempted murder.